Reasoning: The paper discusses the computational complexity of the Colouring problem for various graph classes, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and computer science. The paper also considers variants of the problem, such as extending partial colourings and using lists of permissible colours. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves the study of graph classes and forbidden subgraphs, which suggests the sub-categories cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible choices.
